      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/Menands,_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The Erie Canal cut through what would become Menands in the 1820s, with bridges built over it to connect the canal and Hudson River lands.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
